  "title": "BIM Modeller",
  "description": "<p><strong>Aedas</strong> is one of the world’s leading architecture design practices with a core mission to create inspiring designs that enhance the built environment and enrich lives — today and for future generations. Aedas leverages on its global network of expertise and deep understanding of local culture to deliver design solutions tailored to the nuances and needs of the communities we design for. We take a holistic design approach to sustainability with the goal of maximising benefits to the natural environment and communities, thereby building a better environment in which to work, live, play, and learn.<br /> <br /><strong>Aeda</strong>s operates from 3 principal Design Centres in Asia, Europe and the Middle East with a global network of 13 offices and over 1,000 staff spanning 4 continents﻿.<br /> <br />With a commitment to design excellence, we offer expertise in Architecture, Interior Design, Master Planning and Urban Design, across a broad range of sectors including Commercial, Residential, Mixed-Use, Education, Hospitality (including Integrated Resorts), Retail, Transportation, Aviation, Civic & Cultural, and Sports & Leisure</p><p><strong>Job Summary:</strong><br />Supports the Interiors Design team (Hospitality) in preparing drawings and documentation.<br /><br /><strong>﻿Key Responsibilities:</strong><br />• Assist in preparing design and technical documentation under supervision.<br />• Assist in preparing statutory documentation under supervision.<br />• Assist with BIM model updates and design coordination under supervision.<br />• Work with Interior Designers and team members to prepare drawings, specifications and models.<br />• Maintain drawing accuracy and documentation consistency using firm standards.<br /><br /><strong>﻿Key Competencies:</strong><br />• Basic technical drafting and digital modelling skills.<br />• Good attention to detail and well organised.<br />• Ability to review own work and contribute to documentation quality.<br />• Awareness of digital delivery tools and digital collaboration workflows.</p><p>Apply Here - https://careers.aedas.com/jobs/7127757-bim-modeller?promotion=1810978-trackable-share-link-application-link</p>",
